      "writtenOn": "2021-06-17T16:05:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is kind of spooky for two reasons:\n- If `parameters` is resized, all the objects inside of it are going to get move-constructed. It is very hard to reason about whether a `skstd::optional\u003cDSLWrapper\u003cDSLVar\u003e\u003e` is going to be a stable pointer after being moved or not. If this is safe, please add a comment addressing this somewhere.\n- It is hard to reason about the meaning of `\u0026**` since both optional and DSLWrapper override * to mean something special.\n\nFor #1, I don\u0027t know the answer.\nFor #2, I think this will read better if (a) we get rid of the optional\u003c\u003e inside the array and (b) unwrap the DSLWrapper using a getter-method instead of *. So we\u0027d have `\u0026parameters.back().get()` or something.",
