        "id": 5640
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-06-29T14:27:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Normal DSL usage doesn\u0027t care about the symbol table, though. Since it\u0027s creating nodes directly, and never having to pull anything out of the symbol table, the symbol table is used only for lifetime management rather than name lookup.\n\nSo I think it\u0027s reasonable to separate the two so normal DSL usage doesn\u0027t touch the symbol table, and this sort of parser usage then requires you to manage them manually.",
      "parentUuid": "3b5d0d74_a9a5e50e",
